            , before me, one of His Majesty's Justices of the Peace for the County of Middlesex, this 19th day of December, 1828. E. GRIFFITH.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290115-195-person1568">MR. GOODGER</persName>
            . I am a surgeon. I saw a piece of lead extracted from the deceased's face - I produced it on the last trial.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290115-195-person1569">
                  THOMAS 
                  SHELTON
               <interp inst="t18290115-195-person1569" type="surname" value="SHELTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290115-195-person1569" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
